description.plain:
Frankie Jahmier Childress (b. on July 6th, 1998), better known by his stage name Comethazine, is a rapper repping East St. Louis. Comethazine said in an interview with Mass Appeal that his name comes from the mix of both his nickname in high school, Cocaine, and the drug Promethazine. He got his “Cocaine” nickname for his light skin as opposed to his friends'.

Comethazine started rapping in his basement a few years prior to his EP, Aloe Vera, dropping on iTunes in August of 2016. After dropping the EP, he gained traction with the songs, “Run It” and “Hella Choppers”.

Comethazine has stated in interviews that his influences include 50 Cent, Chief Keef, and Rick James. He is currently signed to Todd Moscowitz’s Alamo Records.

description.plain:
“Air Max,” originally given the name "POGO” by fans, is the first single off Comethazine’s Bawskee 4. Comethazine raps about guns, killing people and his come up selling drugs.

The song was first previewed on April 18th, 2020, via Instagram post. The song was previewed again, via Instagram story, on August 2nd, 2020, playing more of the chorus. The song was previewed once more on August 24th, 2020, via Instagram post. It previewed the music video with the caption

9.9

The new preview had a different melody than the first preview. This is because the sample did not get cleared, so producer Div had to change the melody of the track.

“Air Max” was finally released on September 9th, 2020, with an accompanying music video. It depicts Comethazine in an abandoned warehouse armed with an RPG-7.

Comethazine the album

description.plain:
This song was first brought up during Comethazine’s interview with TimWestwoodTV. Comethazine claimed that the song would be on his upcoming album, Pandemic, but upon the release, it was nowhere to be found.

On June 24th, 2020, almost three months after Pandemic, Comethazine had posted a photo promoting his upcoming album Bawskee 4. Thug then commented on the post, saying:

I want in young nigga

But upon the albums release, the song wasn’t there.

Comethazine has not spoke about the Young Thug feature since, but has stated multiple times that he “doesn’t fuck with other rappers.” He has even rapped about it, most notable on “FIND HIM!,” where he raps:

No features, I’m better alone, check the stats

Comethazine hasn’t done features on an album since his 2018 album Bawskee, which features Lil Yachty on “Bring Dat Bag Out” and Ugly God on “Let It Eat.”
